42:16.000 --> 42:18.000
Tibetans,

42:18.000 --> 42:20.000
Mongols,

42:20.000 --> 42:22.000
ethnic minorities

42:22.000 --> 42:24.000
and Xinjiang people.

42:24.000 --> 42:26.000
The next question is

42:26.000 --> 42:28.000
that we all know that

42:28.000 --> 42:30.000
there is a law called the Qing Dynasty Law.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.000
But did the Qing Dynasty Law

42:32.000 --> 42:34.000
apply in Tibet?

42:34.000 --> 42:36.000
Did the Qing Dynasty Law

42:36.000 --> 42:38.000
apply in Xinjiang?

42:38.000 --> 42:40.000
In fact, it did not.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
Although the Qing Dynasty Law

42:42.000 --> 42:44.000
applied to most empires,

42:44.000 --> 42:46.000
the Roman Empire

42:46.000 --> 42:48.000
also applied the law to the Jews.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.000
In the Qing Dynasty,

42:50.000 --> 42:52.000
the Mongols still applied

42:52.000 --> 42:54.000
the traditional Mongolian law,

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
while the Tibetans still applied the Tibetan law.

42:56.000 --> 42:58.000
Only the Han people

42:58.000 --> 43:00.000
applied the Qing Dynasty Law.

43:00.000 --> 43:02.000
This is understandable.

43:02.000 --> 43:04.000
When a country is very large

43:04.000 --> 43:06.000
and is an empire,

43:06.000 --> 43:08.000
how could it be possible

43:08.000 --> 43:10.000
to force a Mongolian

43:10.000 --> 43:12.000
to marry in a Confucian way?

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
This is also a question of

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
the cost of rule.

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
In order to maintain the operation of an empire

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
and the coordination of the ethnic groups,

43:22.000 --> 43:24.000
you must use different laws

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
to treat different people.

43:26.000 --> 43:28.000
This is now called

43:28.000 --> 43:30.000
the law pluralism.

43:30.000 --> 43:32.000
Does Taiwan want to do the same thing?

43:32.000 --> 43:34.000
Should the indigenous people

43:34.000 --> 43:36.000
apply the indigenous law

43:36.000 --> 43:38.000
or not?

43:38.000 --> 43:40.000
From the perspective of China,

43:40.000 --> 43:42.000
in 1842,

43:42.000 --> 43:44.000
the British said

43:44.000 --> 43:46.000
that they wanted to

43:46.000 --> 43:48.000
apply the British law in China.

43:48.000 --> 43:50.000
Think about it.

43:50.000 --> 43:52.000
What's wrong with

43:52.000 --> 43:54.000
the Mongolians

43:54.000 --> 43:56.000
applying the Mongolian law

43:56.000 --> 43:58.000
and the British applying the British law?

43:58.000 --> 44:00.000
At that time,

44:00.000 --> 44:02.000
foreigners could only

44:02.000 --> 44:04.000
move around

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
when they came to China.

44:06.000 --> 44:08.000
Basically,

44:08.000 --> 44:10.000
it did not affect the original life of the Han people.

44:10.000 --> 44:12.000
Therefore,

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
there is nothing wrong with

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
giving you a piece of land

44:16.000 --> 44:18.000
and having your own law.

44:18.000 --> 44:20.000
In 1842,

44:20.000 --> 44:22.000
foreigners were limited to Guangzhou.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
We call it the Guangzhou system.

44:24.000 --> 44:26.000
Originally in Guangzhou,

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
in 1842,

44:28.000 --> 44:30.000
China had already admitted

44:30.000 --> 44:32.000
that the Americans could apply the British law

44:32.000 --> 44:34.000
in Guangzhou.

44:34.000 --> 44:36.000
Therefore, in 1842 and 1844,

44:36.000 --> 44:38.000
foreigners came to China

44:38.000 --> 44:40.000
and told the negotiators

44:40.000 --> 44:42.000
that they wanted to apply the foreign law.

44:42.000 --> 44:44.000
The Chinese thought it was good,

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
so they gave it to them.

44:46.000 --> 44:48.000
However, in 1868,

44:48.000 --> 44:50.000
