a formal court in China.

55:35.000 --> 55:37.000
Therefore,

55:37.000 --> 55:39.000
we often hear the term

55:39.000 --> 55:41.000
consular trial.

55:41.000 --> 55:43.000
What is a consular trial?

55:43.000 --> 55:45.000
It is when a diplomat

55:45.000 --> 55:47.000
consulates as a judge.

55:47.000 --> 55:49.000
He will be sent to the local consulate

55:49.000 --> 55:51.000
to be tried.

55:51.000 --> 55:53.000
Who is a judge?

55:53.000 --> 55:55.000
It is a diplomat.

55:55.000 --> 55:57.000
Sometimes,

55:57.000 --> 55:59.000
this diplomat also has some legislative powers.

55:59.000 --> 56:01.000
This is a tricky situation.

56:01.000 --> 56:03.000
When the U.S. criticized

56:03.000 --> 56:05.000
China's law of non-discrimination

56:05.000 --> 56:07.000
and non-civilization,

56:07.000 --> 56:09.000
the U.S. did not discriminate.

56:09.000 --> 56:11.000
The diplomat is an executive,

56:11.000 --> 56:13.000
